node.text:
I’m Happy. I woke up living the perfect morning realizing I’ve created a life I absolutely love ❤️ ⁣
⁣
Woke up, made my energize, baked this DELCIOUS zucchini oatmeal breakfast bake in my pajamas, pressed play to a workout while it was in the oven, took a long hot shower, got ready for the day, enjoyed my breakfast on the patio, and now I get to work in the comfort of my home doing something that absolutely fills my heart! Chatting with other women, helping others reach health and wellness goals, making friendships, and doing zoom calls to move my business forward. Another day of having a moment feeling SO thankful for never giving up on this vision of how I wanted life to be. Hard work and consistency with a side of passion and patience helped me create a life I LOVE 🙌🏻 ⁣
⁣
Ok, now here’s the recipe to this deliciousness☺️ *swipe over for video⁣
⁣
-2 cups oats ⁣
-1/2 cup nuts ( I used trail mix I had with nuts and fruit) ⁣
-1/4 maple syrup⁣
-1 tsp baking powder⁣
-1.5 tsp cinnamon ⁣
-2 cups milk (I used almond milk)⁣
-1 large egg⁣
-2 tsp melted coconut oil⁣
-2 tsp vanilla extract (I used rum extract it’s all I had)⁣
-1.5 cups grated zucchini (squeeze water out) ⁣
⁣
First mix dry ingredients and then add wet ingredients! Put in 8x8 baking dish and bake for 40 mins @ 375 degrees F ⁣
⁣
ENJOY! ⁣
⁣
I topped mine with PB and redi whip!

node.text:
If it’s your first time carrying a child or your 5th, you understand how the worry never goes away. ⁣⁣
I remember the long days between seeing a positive test to our first ultrasound. I thought once we heard a heartbeat we’d be “in the clear of worrying” and at relief. Then the worry came from 2 days in a row of not having morning sickness and wondering why, what was going?! So you worried again. Then one day the new worry was because I felt like my belly wasn’t growing overtime, and wondered why. Recently, having uncommon reactions with my body threw in a new worry of what was going on and if everything is OK. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Carrying this child is the most heart filling, exciting thing I’ve ever experienced but it’s also the most concerning, emotionally stressful thing. What I’ve realized of 17+ weeks of being a mother to a child is that the worry began and will never leave. There will always be a concern or worry being parent to something you love so dearly. But you worry because you care. You worry because you love your little baby so much already. As a mother, you have another life in your hands and that comes with so so much to face in a day. We wouldn’t trade it for the world, and it’s OK to feel your emotions through every season of being a momma. 🖤 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Grateful for another good doctors appointment and hearing a strong healthy heartbeat! You are loved so much already, baby P! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
P.s. Sharing our journey of finding out we were pregnant with our miracle because I haven’t shared yet 🙂 our full story is in my IGTV videos

node.text:
A question I get asked every morning is how I do my Bible study and how I deepened my faith in 2020. ⁣
I know if you got asked to remove one year of your life most would probably choose 2020.... but to be honest, 2020 was the most important year of my life thus far. It completely changed my faith, my view of life and every day circumstances, and my feelings as a person. When I started this Bible study and spent a half hour at the beginning of every day reading and understanding the Bible, my life changed more and more every single day. I searched for 25 years to find something that I would understand this well and guide me the way this app does. So I share this just in case there’s someone out there who needed this like I did, because if it wasn’t shared from a woman on social media I wouldn’t know about it 😞🙏🏼❤️⁣
The app: @thedailygraceco 
Bible:⁣ @valee_of_vision 
Bible tabs:⁣ Amazon
Devotion:⁣ Unshakable from Amazon
⁣
*I 100% respect everyone’s choice of faith and religion! This post is simply to just share what has worked for me and maybe for any other Christians wanting to deepen their faith or anyone wanting to understand the Bible better 💖 ⁣
P.s. video quality shows you how outdated my husbands phone is 🙈🤨

It’s been awhile since I’ve showed how I make my smoothie! Honestly, I switch it up a lot! This has been my go to way to make it lately! I went live in my challenge group and shared this tutorial and now the ladies are hooked too ☺️ quite honestly, these ingredients don’t sound that great together but you👏🏽have👏🏽to👏🏽try👏🏽it! I’m a HUGE icecream lover so this hits the spot for me every single day. It’s that sweet milkshake I get but this one makes my body feel BETTER rather than worse. ⁣
⁣
*𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐦𝐨𝐭𝐞𝐬 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡𝐲 𝐰𝐞𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐥𝐨𝐬𝐬⁣
*𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐬 𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐫𝐠𝐲⁣
*𝐝𝐞𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐬 𝐜𝐫𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬⁣
*𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐛𝐥𝐨𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠⁣
*𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡⁣
*𝐝𝐞𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐝 𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐨𝐥 & 𝐛𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐮𝐫𝐞 ⁣
*𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐢𝐧𝐟𝐥𝐚𝐦𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 ⁣
*𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐢𝐦𝐦𝐮𝐧𝐞 𝐬𝐲𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐦⁣
*𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐥𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐬 𝐝𝐚𝐢𝐥𝐲 𝐯𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐬⁣
*𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡𝐲 𝐝𝐢𝐠𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧⁣
*𝐦𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐟𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐚𝐥 𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 ⁣
 ⁣
I’ve been consuming this daily for 38 months now and I’ll continue to stay committed 🥳👏🏽💪🏻💃🏼

node.text:
Kate and I met through TikTok and now we have become good friends! We decided to have lunch together and chat it out! I also tried a new recipe that was SO GOOD! 

Flatout wrap in the airfryer for 7 mins at 375. Then top with avocado, chicken, feta cheese, and BBQ. Put back in airfryer for 5 mins! 🤤

node.text:
𝗪𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞 𝐢𝐬 𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭, 𝐈, 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐋𝐨𝐫𝐝, 𝐰𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐞 𝐢𝐭 𝐡𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐞𝐧. ~ 𝐈𝐬𝐚𝐢𝐚𝐡 𝟔𝟎:𝟐𝟐⁣
⁣
Wow. Such a full circle moment today. 4 years ago, when I FIRST became a coach, I made 3 long term/bigger goals to work towards. One of them being to be asked by corporate to speak on our weekly National Wake Up call to the entire network of coaches…. And today I got to check off that goal 🙏🏼❤️ ⁣
⁣
You know, last night I was laying there with all of the thoughts rolling through my head (because sleep is currently not a thing anymore for this lady 🙃), and all I could think about was timing. Gods plans, Gods timing, our vision for when we think something should happen but then looking back and realizing when it DID happen it ended up being so perfect…⁣
Last year I remember thinking “will I be asked soon?” “Why haven’t I been asked yet?” “Should I request to speak?” “Will I ever get asked?” “If I speak one day will the call be a disappointment to the viewers?” So many questions on the timing and future.⁣
𝘓𝘰𝘰𝘬𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘣𝘢𝘤𝘬 𝘯𝘰𝘸, 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘸𝘢𝘪𝘵 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘯𝘦𝘦𝘥𝘦𝘥. 𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘨𝘳𝘰𝘸𝘵𝘩 𝘐 𝘮𝘢𝘥𝘦 𝘧𝘳𝘰𝘮 𝘸𝘩𝘦𝘯 𝘐 𝘵𝘩𝘰𝘶𝘨𝘩𝘵 𝘐 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘥𝘺 𝘵𝘰 𝘵𝘰𝘥𝘢𝘺 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘯𝘦𝘦𝘥𝘦𝘥. The way it went was perfect. ⁣
⁣
Such a reminder for me to once again trust the journey, trust the timing, and “when the time is right, He, the Lord, will make it happen”…⁣
⁣
So grateful for the love, the messages, the support, the good luck flowers from my husband this morning, the women I get to call my teammates by my side daily… it all means the world to me! ⁣
⁣
Don’t give up on your goals, your visions, your passion, or your journey. It all will unfold EXACTLY how and when it’s meant to for the perfect outcome. 🖤

node.text:
Me to all of the women up ordering their pumpkin spice lattes and shopping fall decor: “sit yo booties down! It’s not your time yet! SUMMERS STILL HERE!”⁣
⁣
All while sitting on my couch ordering fall shackets and booties 🤭🙈🙃😅 ⁣
⁣
Really though, I dread fall and winter like I dread laundry… the last few years Ive struggled really bad mentally during winter living in South Dakota. So cold and dark with no fresh air. BUT! Fall clothing is something I can handle! 🤪 Maybe I’m just excited to be able to wear something besides a comfy dress and leggings #pregantlife ⁣
⁣
I don’t decorate my house for the season but I go all out in the wardrobe category 😜⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
Got 2 new shackets and a pair of brown booties from @gliksofficial with my birthday gift card and I’m LOVING the shacket trend this fall! I shared on my stories the link to them so head over and watch my try on! ⁣
⁣
Which look is your favorite?? ⁣
⁣
#shackets #fallfashion #35weeks #35weekspregnant #8monthspregnant #momtobe #glikfluencer #falloutfits #southdakota

node.text:
I’m Happy. I woke up living the perfect morning realizing I’ve created a life I absolutely love ❤️ ⁣
⁣
Woke up, made my energize, baked this DELCIOUS zucchini oatmeal breakfast bake in my pajamas, pressed play to a workout while it was in the oven, took a long hot shower, got ready for the day, enjoyed my breakfast on the patio, and now I get to work in the comfort of my home doing something that absolutely fills my heart! Chatting with other women, helping others reach health and wellness goals, making friendships, and doing zoom calls to move my business forward. Another day of having a moment feeling SO thankful for never giving up on this vision of how I wanted life to be. Hard work and consistency with a side of passion and patience helped me create a life I LOVE 🙌🏻 ⁣
⁣
Ok, now here’s the recipe to this deliciousness☺️ *swipe over for video⁣
⁣
-2 cups oats ⁣
-1/2 cup nuts ( I used trail mix I had with nuts and fruit) ⁣
-1/4 maple syrup⁣
-1 tsp baking powder⁣
-1.5 tsp cinnamon ⁣
-2 cups milk (I used almond milk)⁣
-1 large egg⁣
-2 tsp melted coconut oil⁣
-2 tsp vanilla extract (I used rum extract it’s all I had)⁣
-1.5 cups grated zucchini (squeeze water out) ⁣
⁣
First mix dry ingredients and then add wet ingredients! Put in 8x8 baking dish and bake for 40 mins @ 375 degrees F ⁣
⁣
ENJOY! ⁣
⁣
I topped mine with PB and redi whip!

node.text:
⁣
𝐈𝐭’𝐬 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐝𝐢𝐫𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 ⁣
⁣
This was actually the headline message from yesterday’s church service but it got me to thinking of how it pertains to so many aspects of our life. ⁣
⁣
Why is that we have it decided in our heads it’s either perfection or failure…? ⁣
“If I can’t be all in, I might as well not start”. ⁣
“I didn’t give 100% effort today so I failed”⁣
“What’s the points of showing up if it’s only a little bit?”⁣
⁣
To get closer to our goals and where we want to be, all we need is action and “better”. It doesn’t need to be perfection, it just needs to be movement 𝘧𝘰𝘳𝘸𝘢𝘳𝘥 in a better direction. You’re better off showing up every day for a long period time making BETTER choices than you are to show up striving for perfection because I’m here to tell you 𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘧𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘤𝘢𝘯𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘣𝘦 𝘥𝘰𝘯𝘦 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 𝘤𝘰𝘯𝘴𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘺. We are human. Perfection isn’t sustainable. ⁣
⁣
So today, on this beautiful Monday we were blessed with, let’s focus on small BETTER steps in the right direction vs perfection ❤️ it will make the journey to our goals much more enjoyable…

node.text:
I want to tell you one thing I learned at the beginning of my health and fitness journey…⁣
⁣
The beginning is the hardest part. Personally… this is how it went for me.⁣
Week 1 of starting a new program and changing my habits: my body was sore, I felt tired, my motivation was hard to find, and most of all my thoughts were telling me every negative reason and excuse to quit. ⁣
⁣
Week 2: I kept asking myself if it was going to be worth it, I hadn’t seen changes in my body yet, I had thoughts of discourage, and I felt that burnout feeling already⁣
⁣
Week 3: I was finally starting to notice I had more energy, things were starting to become habits, I felt myself having more positive thoughts towards my journey, my ambition increased, and I was experiencing small changes in my body that sparked a fire in me. ⁣
⁣
So if I can give you one piece of advice, right through the beginning. Fight through the start because it truly is the hardest part. When you’re not feeling the energy boost yet, when you’re not seeing results yet, when you’re breaking negative habits and trying to create new positive ones, when you’re body is sore, and when your mean girl in your head feels stronger than you are… FIGHT THROUGH and don’t stop. It truly does take 21 days to build new habits and it takes time for our bodies to change. I can promise you that 3 months into it you’ll look back with a smile waking up daily realizing that a lot of things that were super hard for you in the past are now your daily HABITS. It’s amazing how a workout, fueling my body with nutrient dense foods, and increasing water intake changes my entire day around. More energy, clearer skin, positive thoughts, confidence, less body pains and doctor visits, and relationships with my loved one improved. ⁣
⁣
Today I proudly complete my 6 week boxing program! Showing up for 30 minutes a day in my living room to put my health (physically and mentally) first. 🙌🏻 onto my next one starting Monday morning! It’s a 4 week program and hopefully will lead me right to baby time 😍🥳⁣
How crazy is that?! 
.
.
@eqylactivewear code: HaileyP 

#34weekspregnant #34weeks #thirdtrimester #athomeworkouts #fitnessapparel #healthjourney
